public boolean isPowerOfThree(int n) {
    if (n == 1) return true;
    if (n % 3 == 0) return isPowerOfThree(n / 3);
    return false;
}
```


Explanation:
The solution is a standard recursive solution to check if a given number is a power of three. The base case is when the number is 1, which is considered a power of 3. Otherwise, we check if the number is divisible by 3 without a remainder (i.e., it is a multiple of 3). In that case, we recursively call the function on the divided number. If the number is not divisible by 3, then it is not a power of 3. We return false in this case.

This algorithm effectively checks if the given number can be expressed as 3 to some power. The recursion stops when the base case is reached, and the result is returned up the call stack. This approach ensures that we do not have loops, as the recursion eventually terminates.

